        "summary": "Imam al-Sadiq (AS) was asked to define the ascetic (zahid) in this world. He provided a profound definition: the true ascetic avoids not only the haram (forbidden) out of fear of divine punishment, but also avoids the halal (permissible) out of fear of being questioned about it on the Day of Judgment. This teaching, transmitted through a chain of Imams including al-Rida and Musa al-Kadhim, reflects the elevated standard of spiritual discipline in Shia ethics where accountability extends even to permissible enjoyments.",
        "key_terms": {
